Let's go inside.

256
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:19,283
Just let go of me.
Why did you bring me to the morgue?

257
00:19:20,075 --> 00:19:23,203
Honey, what are you doing here?

258
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:26,290
What's going on?

259
00:19:27,082 --> 00:19:28,625
Where is Jong-chul?

260
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:32,337
Jong-chul…

261
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:35,465
Jong-chul!

262
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:39,386
Jong-chul!

263
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:44,308
DECEASED PARK JONG-CHUL

264
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:49,521
Oh my god… My baby!

265
00:19:51,398 --> 00:19:52,566
Oh my…

266
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:54,902
Jong-chul!

267
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:05,412
Smells good.

268
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:07,664
You're eating now?

269
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:10,292
9 LABOR ACTIVISTS ARRESTED

270
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:13,086
YOON SANG-SAM,
JOURNALIST, <i>DONGA DAILY</i>

271
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:16,673
Sang-sam wrote a killer article
on the labor activist movement.

272
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:19,218
A beautiful piece of work.

273
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:20,469
What's the point?

274
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:22,971
We can only print what they allow us.

275
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:26,975
It's the stuff between the lines, pops.

276
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,770
Leaving some room for interpretation.

277
00:20:29,853 --> 00:20:32,356
Not when they spell it out for you.

278
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:36,610
You're prickly today.
Did you fight with the wife again?

279
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:39,363
-<i>Joongang Daily</i>!
-Just say you're sorry.

280
00:20:39,446 --> 00:20:41,114
Joongang's late today.

281
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:43,033
3:00 P.M. JANUARY 15, 1987
PROSECUTORS' PRESS ROOM

282
00:20:43,116 --> 00:20:44,660
Let's see how their dictation is.

283
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:53,835
Shit! Come on.

284
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:56,421
-What's going on?
-Give me one, too!

285
00:20:57,297 --> 00:21:00,884
-Not the front page. The other page.
-The current affairs section!

286
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:03,595
-I can't fucking believe this.
-What the hell is going on?

287
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:06,431
-Where is it?
-Which hospital?

288
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:13,522
Chief, I just saw the article.

289
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:16,066
Who cross-checked the info?

290
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:18,151
That's the least of my worries!

291
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:21,154
The military just stormed
into our offices.

292
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:23,448
What?

293
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:27,452
You said you checked all the facts.

294
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:30,497
They don't care about that!
We violated journalism guidelines.

295
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:31,581
Where is the Current Affairs?

296
00:21:31,665 --> 00:21:34,459
Find somewhere to lay low and stay there.

297
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:36,837
If they catch you,
you'll be beaten to death.

298
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:40,424
<i>-Do you hear me?
-I found him!</i>

299
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,552
-What the hell?
-Come here!

300
00:21:44,511 --> 00:21:45,762
<i>What the hell? Let go!</i>

301
00:21:46,346 --> 00:21:47,431
<i>Who are you?</i>

302
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,476
<i>Let go of me!</i>

303
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:55,439
I'm so sorry, sir!

304
00:21:56,231 --> 00:22:00,694
I'll do everything in my power
to contain the situation, sir!

305
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:03,613
COMMISSIONER GENERAL
POLICE HEADQUARTERS

306
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:09,244
It seems like we've worked
ourselves into a corner.

307
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:12,122
Things like this happen
while conducting national affairs.

308
00:22:12,205 --> 00:22:13,582
It will work itself out.

309
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:14,624
Shut up!

310
00:22:15,459 --> 00:22:17,753
It could cost us our necks!

311
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,509
Cut out the ego bullshit. Sit down.

312
00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:30,807
The President threw the papers
to the floor.

313
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:33,685
This is serious.

314
00:22:35,645 --> 00:22:38,607
We have to put out the fire first.

315
00:22:39,649 --> 00:22:41,151
Read this at the press briefing.

316
00:22:45,363 --> 00:22:47,991
LEFTIST STUDENT DIES OF HEART ATTACK

317
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:49,951
So that's what happened.

318
00:22:50,827 --> 00:22:55,749
And I swear on the honor of the police,

319
00:22:56,416 --> 00:22:59,211
there was no excessive force employed.

320
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:02,047
Then how did he die?

321
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:06,051
Well, it seems that…
During the investigation,

322
00:23:06,134 --> 00:23:08,512
the investigator slammed his hands…

323
00:23:11,681 --> 00:23:12,974
on the table and…

324
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:14,684
Please continue.

325
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:18,146
The student was terrified.

326
00:23:19,439 --> 00:23:23,151
So when the investigator slammed
his hands on the table, he just…

327
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:31,034
-He just dropped dead.
-What?

328
00:23:32,285 --> 00:23:34,287
Does that make any sense?

329
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:37,082
Dying from someone slamming
their hands on a table?

330
00:23:37,165 --> 00:23:39,584
The official cause of death
is a heart attack.

331
00:23:39,668 --> 00:23:42,587
A perfectly healthy young man
had a heart attack

332
00:23:42,671 --> 00:23:43,755
by sudden shock?

333
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:47,467
A doctor from Chungang Hospital
confirmed this case.

334
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:50,137
What's the doctor's name?

335
00:23:51,054 --> 00:23:53,098
His name?

336
00:23:55,058 --> 00:23:58,854
-Oh, what was his name?
-It hasn't been confirmed yet, right?

337
00:23:58,937 --> 00:24:02,732
Of course it has.
The doctor's name is Oh Yun-sang.

338
00:24:02,816 --> 00:24:05,485
-Did you get that?
-Oh Yun-sang, Chungang Hospital.

339
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:08,989
-Let's go to Chungang Hospital!
-Find Oh Yun-sang!

340
00:24:09,072 --> 00:24:10,782
-Let's go.
-It's Oh Yun-sang!

341
00:24:16,037 --> 00:24:19,583
I said too much, didn't I?

342
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:22,460
Sorry…

343
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,971
CHUNGANG UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

344
00:24:33,054 --> 00:24:34,222
Out of my way!

345
00:24:41,855 --> 00:24:44,482
So he died of heart attack
from sudden shock?

346
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:49,362
Well, I can't comment until
the autopsy has been completed--

347
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:51,114
Was he still alive at the ER?

348
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:53,825
He didn't come to the ER.
I saw him in Namyeong-dong…

349
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:56,703
Namyeong-dong? What did you do?

350
00:24:56,786 --> 00:25:00,332
I arrived after
the cardiac arrest occurred.

351
00:25:00,415 --> 00:25:01,958
Give us more details.

352
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:06,254
I mean, after I arrived at the scene,
I dried the body,

353
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:07,839
then checked the--

354
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:09,424
The kid was wet?

355
00:25:11,551 --> 00:25:13,220
We need details.

356
00:25:14,304 --> 00:25:16,014
Are you saying the body was wet?

357
00:25:16,097 --> 00:25:18,808
The detectives said…

358
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:21,853
They said that the deceased
was heavily intoxicated,

359
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:24,397
so he drank a lot of water
during the investigation.

360
00:25:24,481 --> 00:25:25,941
He was heavily intoxicated?

361
00:25:27,067 --> 00:25:28,610
He'd been drinking rice wine…

362
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:30,070
Who is he kidding?

363
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:32,030
So did he die of shock or not?

364
00:25:32,113 --> 00:25:34,491
What should I write?
He didn't give us anything.

365
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:37,661
Why are you even worried?
We will be given guidelines anyway.

366
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:38,912
Do you know any doctor?

367
00:25:38,995 --> 00:25:41,373
If I knew any,
I would already have had an interview.

368
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:47,128
-Stay right here, understood?
-Yes sir.

369
00:25:48,755 --> 00:25:49,965
Where is the restroom?

370
00:25:56,721 --> 00:25:58,181
4:00 P.M. JANUARY 15, 1987
HANYANG UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

371
00:25:58,265 --> 00:25:59,599
Good afternoon, Prosecutor.

372
00:25:59,683 --> 00:26:02,769
Did you bring enough roll films?

373
00:26:02,852 --> 00:26:05,313
I brought ten with me.

374
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:08,066
That's great. Oh, they're here.

375
00:26:10,193 --> 00:26:11,861
I'm Dr. Hwang from the National Crime Lab.

376
00:26:11,945 --> 00:26:13,488
I'll be witnessing.

377
00:26:13,571 --> 00:26:16,658
This is a very sensitive case,
so please do everything by the book.

378
00:26:17,659 --> 00:26:21,538
Make sure to leave no detail out. Got it?

379
00:26:21,621 --> 00:26:24,291
Is this necessary? It's just a formality.

380
00:26:24,374 --> 00:26:27,419
PROSECUTOR PYO
SEOUL DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

381
00:26:29,796 --> 00:26:31,256
Is that how you do your job?

382
00:26:31,339 --> 00:26:32,924
I apologize.

383
00:26:33,925 --> 00:26:34,801
Let's go.

384
00:26:41,308 --> 00:26:42,267
Who are you people?

385
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:45,270
-Just piss off.
-Who told you to do an autopsy?

386
00:26:46,021 --> 00:26:48,732
We have an official order for an autopsy.

387
00:26:48,815 --> 00:26:51,693
We heard nothing about it,
so it's not happening.

388
00:26:51,776 --> 00:26:53,820
I'm a public prosecutor!

389
00:26:53,903 --> 00:26:58,491
Oh, really? We're sorry for our insolence.

390
00:26:59,326 --> 00:27:01,494
Jong-chul!

391
00:27:01,578 --> 00:27:03,913
-Stop!
-Jong-chul!

392
00:27:09,544 --> 00:27:11,087
-Let go of me!
-Hey!

393
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:13,048
Leave her alone!

394
00:27:13,631 --> 00:27:15,342
-Mom!
-Mom!

395
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:20,555
Let me see him for the last time.

396
00:27:20,638 --> 00:27:23,350
This is my last chance. Please…

397
00:27:23,433 --> 00:27:25,810
-Get her out of here.
-Please just for a moment.

398
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:29,230
-Come on.
-Please for the last time!

399
00:27:29,314 --> 00:27:32,859
-Let me touch his hand!
-Get her out of here!

400
00:27:32,942 --> 00:27:34,611
Please let me see him…

401
00:27:42,035 --> 00:27:43,495
What are you here for?

402
00:27:43,578 --> 00:27:46,456
Did you smirk at me?
I'll remember your faces.

403
00:27:46,998 --> 00:27:48,249
Fucking thugs!

404
00:27:48,792 --> 00:27:51,378
KIM JUNG-NAM SPY RING

405
00:27:52,754 --> 00:27:53,797
JANG YEONG-DAL ARRESTED

406
00:28:00,929 --> 00:28:03,264
KIM JUNG-NAM

407
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:06,726
I think you should take this.

408
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:11,648
Who is this?

409
00:28:11,731 --> 00:28:14,317
<i>This is Prosecutor Choi with
the Seoul District Prosecutors' Office.</i>

410
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:17,278
I'm at Hanyang University Hospital,

411
00:28:17,362 --> 00:28:20,365
and your men are refusing to cooperate.

412
00:28:21,116 --> 00:28:23,660
<i>I've been through this with
the necessary people.</i>

413
00:28:23,743 --> 00:28:25,412
<i>That autopsy isn't happening.</i>

414
00:28:26,996 --> 00:28:29,416
Old man, I don't like
your condescending tone.

415
00:28:29,499 --> 00:28:31,376
I'm the Director of
Anti-communist Investigations.

416
00:28:31,459 --> 00:28:34,838
<i>And that puts you above the law?</i>

417
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:37,882
<i>Should I send over
some of my boys to teach you?</i>

418
00:28:37,966 --> 00:28:38,925
What did you say?

419
00:28:39,008 --> 00:28:43,680
Open your books and check
who has the jurisdiction here.

420
00:28:44,514 --> 00:28:49,561
And you better lose that accent
before you're mistaken for Kim Il Sung.

421
00:28:59,404 --> 00:29:01,030
Get the car out.

422
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:02,115
Yes, sir.

423
00:29:10,039 --> 00:29:12,125
That crazy fucker!

424
00:29:13,918 --> 00:29:15,211
What the hell?

425
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:31,186
This is the official order
for the autopsy.

426
00:29:31,269 --> 00:29:34,397
Nice work hiding behind a piece of paper.

427
00:29:35,565 --> 00:29:38,067
Let's not make a scene.
We will do this by the book.

428
00:29:44,157 --> 00:29:47,952
If hunting dogs miss their target
while fighting among themselves,

429
00:29:49,370 --> 00:29:53,333
who do you think the master
is going to punish for this?

430
00:29:53,416 --> 00:29:56,336
I consider myself a stray
without a master.

431
00:29:56,419 --> 00:30:00,632
You better watch yourself.
I'm liable to bite anyone.

432
00:30:00,715 --> 00:30:02,008
Is that right?

433
00:30:02,675 --> 00:30:06,179
But only your jaws will hurt.

434
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:15,772
Wait.

435
00:30:19,275 --> 00:30:21,861
My father's cousin's daughter

436
00:30:22,570 --> 00:30:26,950
just married a journalist
from this foreign newspaper.

437
00:30:27,033 --> 00:30:30,286
Peter Henderson something or other.

438
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:33,957
He's been hounding me
for a story recently.

439
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:35,625
Jeez.

440
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:39,796
The President would be quite upset
to read about this in the foreign press

441
00:30:39,879 --> 00:30:41,506
before the Seoul Olympics.

442
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:52,100
What is it that you want?

443
00:30:52,934 --> 00:30:57,605
I don't fucking want anything.
I just want to do my job right.

444
00:30:58,439 --> 00:30:59,482
All right.

445
00:31:00,733 --> 00:31:02,360
Go for it, then.

446
00:31:04,112 --> 00:31:06,072
It's not going to change anything.

447
00:31:11,286 --> 00:31:12,537
Let's get out of here.

448
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:18,001
I'm doing the autopsy.

449
00:31:18,084 --> 00:31:20,253
I got your neck.

450
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:24,173
Go wander the streets
with the rest of the strays.

451
00:31:30,471 --> 00:31:32,932
I guess I just dug my own grave.

452
00:31:38,146 --> 00:31:39,939
I'll have to drink soju from now.

453
00:31:47,363 --> 00:31:50,783
9:50 P.M. JANUARY 15, 1987
HANYANG UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

454
00:31:55,455 --> 00:31:58,291
Are you with the victim's family?
Your name, please.

455
00:32:00,209 --> 00:32:02,629
Park Wol-gil, I'm Jong-chul's uncle.

456
00:32:02,712 --> 00:32:06,049
Please take a seat.

457
00:32:06,132 --> 00:32:07,842
Shall we?

458
00:32:40,416 --> 00:32:41,793
I'm going to the restroom.

459
00:32:57,684 --> 00:33:00,561
Doctor, I'm a journalist from <i>Donga Daily</i>.

460
00:33:01,771 --> 00:33:03,314
Did you see any signs of torture?

461
00:33:05,316 --> 00:33:07,485
I waited here for too long.

462
00:33:09,195 --> 00:33:13,116
You said the body was wet.
What was the condition of the body?

463
00:33:15,702 --> 00:33:17,286
Just tell me what you saw.

464
00:33:19,622 --> 00:33:20,540
Doctor!

465
00:33:24,752 --> 00:33:29,132
There was water everywhere on the floor.

466
00:33:32,635 --> 00:33:34,387
And there was a bathtub in the room.

467
00:33:39,684 --> 00:33:41,728
I heard crackling in the lungs.

468
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,022
Crackles?

469
00:33:44,731 --> 00:33:46,899
Do you confirm the cause of death?

470
00:33:52,655 --> 00:33:53,948
Yes.

471
00:34:08,588 --> 00:34:09,714
Stop them!

472
00:34:10,423 --> 00:34:11,674
No pictures!

473
00:34:12,675 --> 00:34:14,552
Please say a word. Please!

474
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:17,722
-Mr. Park!
-Any comments?

475
00:34:17,805 --> 00:34:19,390
The police murdered him!

476
00:34:19,974 --> 00:34:21,893
The police murdered him!

477
00:34:23,102 --> 00:34:27,815
My nephew didn't die of shock.
He was murdered!

478
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:30,068
He was killed during torture, wasn't he?

479
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:33,404
He was tortured with water, right?

480
00:34:48,044 --> 00:34:50,171
This is what you'll say
when you give your statement tomorrow.

481
00:34:51,255 --> 00:34:52,423
They're aware of it, too.

482
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:57,261
But I only dropped by to give them a hand.

483
00:34:58,304 --> 00:35:01,849
There are formalities to go through.
Think of it as an early vacation.

484
00:35:02,642 --> 00:35:04,102
I know you're good at lying.

485
00:35:04,185 --> 00:35:06,813
I don't deserve this.

486
00:35:08,648 --> 00:35:11,317
How dare you question my authority?

487
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:14,070
I did everything exactly as I was told.

488
00:35:14,904 --> 00:35:16,447
-Why should I--
-Han-kyung.

489
00:35:19,617 --> 00:35:20,785
Yes, Director.

490
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:24,163
Just go along with it.

491
00:35:31,129 --> 00:35:32,046
As you command, sir.

492
00:35:32,130 --> 00:35:34,215
-We have to run the story
-What's going on?

493
00:35:34,298 --> 00:35:36,342
before they wipe it under the carpet.

494
00:35:36,425 --> 00:35:38,761
I even got my arm broken.
I have nothing to fear!

495
00:35:38,845 --> 00:35:40,513
-Did he find something?
-Will you take the responsibility?

496
00:35:40,596 --> 00:35:42,557
-We should be responsible?
-For what?

497
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,016
Wait. He's coming.

498
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:46,269
-You alright, man?
-What happened?

499
00:35:46,894 --> 00:35:48,813
-Let's go.
-Where are you going?

500
00:35:48,896 --> 00:35:50,148
Attention, everyone!

501
00:35:51,232 --> 00:35:53,484
From tomorrow, we're running a special
on torture prevention.

502
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:54,527
What?

503
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:58,781
Launch a task force
to find out who killed him and how.

504
00:35:58,865 --> 00:36:00,366
What about the guidelines?

505
00:36:04,662 --> 00:36:05,746
Fuck that!

506
00:36:06,747 --> 00:36:07,665
Just fuck it!

507
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:11,210
The police tortured and killed a student!

508
00:36:11,752 --> 00:36:15,464
I don't give a rat's ass about
goddamn guidelines.

509
00:36:16,090 --> 00:36:17,049
Yes sir.

510
00:36:34,233 --> 00:36:37,904
Dr. Hwang! I really appreciate
you going through all of this.

511
