1019
01:16:50,397 --> 01:16:52,065
<i>And your last chance.</i>

1020
01:16:54,860 --> 01:16:56,862
THE BLUE HOUSE

1021
01:17:00,824 --> 01:17:01,992
Release them all.

1022
01:17:03,869 --> 01:17:07,789
At a time like this, we have got to
bring in more, not release them.

1023
01:17:07,873 --> 01:17:10,542
When I was living in the North,

1024
01:17:11,752 --> 01:17:13,420
I had a dog that used to run away.

1025
01:17:15,047 --> 01:17:17,382
Do you want to know how I always found it?

1026
01:17:21,094 --> 01:17:23,847
I'd go for a walk
with a female dog in heat.

1027
01:17:24,598 --> 01:17:29,227
Without fail, the runaway dog
would come out running and drooling.

1028
01:17:31,730 --> 01:17:32,939
<i>I've decided that</i>

1029
01:17:33,982 --> 01:17:37,861
<i>it is impossible to revise
the constitution during my term.</i>

1030
01:17:38,737 --> 01:17:43,367
<i>In order to assure a peaceful transition
of power, my term will terminate</i>

1031
01:17:43,450 --> 01:17:45,285
<i>on the 25th of February, next year…</i>

1032
01:17:45,369 --> 01:17:47,663
Jung-nam can't help
but crawl out of his hole now.

1033
01:17:48,872 --> 01:17:51,708
Use his bitches as baits.

1034
01:17:52,668 --> 01:17:53,669
As you command, sir.

1035
01:17:55,671 --> 01:17:56,713
-Follow me.
-Yes, sir.

1036
01:17:57,214 --> 01:17:58,674
Hey, take that one, too.

1037
01:18:00,300 --> 01:18:05,222
<i>…and those who seek to divide the nation…</i>

1038
01:18:06,181 --> 01:18:07,933
That's bullshit. How can he do this?

1039
01:18:08,684 --> 01:18:11,520
Direct election is out of the question.

1040
01:18:11,603 --> 01:18:14,564
This is a blatant extension
of dictatorship.

1041
01:18:14,648 --> 01:18:15,899
What does this mean for us?

1042
01:18:15,982 --> 01:18:18,443
Get ready to be busy as hell.

1043
01:18:18,527 --> 01:18:22,406
Politics! Current Affairs! Gather up!

1044
01:18:26,451 --> 01:18:27,619
What does this mean?

1045
01:18:27,703 --> 01:18:30,455
That means he will choose
the next President himself.

1046
01:18:31,123 --> 01:18:33,041
Fuck! One more <i>soju</i> here.

1047
01:18:33,125 --> 01:18:35,085
-Coming up.
-No, we're good.

1048
01:18:37,295 --> 01:18:39,589
Attorney Choi,
you have a trial in an hour.

1049
01:18:43,135 --> 01:18:44,302
Fuck trial.

1050
01:18:45,971 --> 01:18:49,057
That son of a bitch. So he's going to rule
for another seven years?

1051
01:18:49,141 --> 01:18:50,851
Not just seven.

1052
01:18:50,934 --> 01:18:53,687
He'll hold power as long
as they hold elections in the gym.

1053
01:18:53,770 --> 01:18:55,605
What's that mean?

1054
01:18:55,689 --> 01:18:58,316
Indirect elections, you dumb ass.

1055
01:18:58,400 --> 01:19:01,027
How did you get into college, man?

1056
01:19:01,111 --> 01:19:04,114
-You're a college student, man.
-Goddamn fixed game.

1057
01:19:05,782 --> 01:19:08,285
-What are you doing?
-We should at least do something.

1058
01:19:09,119 --> 01:19:10,537
Let me help.

1059
01:19:11,329 --> 01:19:13,039
Fire up the printing press.

1060
01:19:13,623 --> 01:19:15,125
-Where is it?
-Over there.

1061
01:19:15,792 --> 01:19:19,421
<i>I have well received the opinion
and the decision of the country,</i>

1062
01:19:19,504 --> 01:19:21,590
<i>and to proceed by accepting it,</i>

1063
01:19:21,673 --> 01:19:26,386
<i>I promise to bring the new future
for the country itself and…</i>

1064
01:19:26,470 --> 01:19:28,722
I need to go out for a moment, Abbot.

1065
01:19:30,515 --> 01:19:32,350
It's too risky to go out like that.

1066
01:19:36,313 --> 01:19:39,274
What's the point of
a direct election anyway?

1067
01:19:39,357 --> 01:19:41,359
I know they pay people for the election.

1068
01:19:41,443 --> 01:19:44,279
You're right.
This country isn't ready for democracy.

1069
01:19:46,031 --> 01:19:47,574
Get ready for your shifts!

1070
01:19:55,373 --> 01:19:58,251
<i>Also, I truly believe
that this direct election</i>

1071
01:19:58,335 --> 01:20:00,504
<i>will bring the new future for the country.</i>

1072
01:20:01,922 --> 01:20:05,717
I've got all of your backs.

1073
01:20:07,761 --> 01:20:09,429
Go out and find every

1074
01:20:10,305 --> 01:20:12,766
commie supporter you can find.

1075
01:20:13,767 --> 01:20:15,811
Eradicate them.

1076
01:20:15,894 --> 01:20:19,439
Eradicate communism!

1077
01:20:24,945 --> 01:20:27,072
We released Kim Jung-nam's bitches.

1078
01:20:33,453 --> 01:20:34,663
Prisoner 4879!

1079
01:20:37,040 --> 01:20:38,333
You have a meeting.

1080
01:20:42,337 --> 01:20:43,296
In here.

1081
01:21:06,069 --> 01:21:08,363
VISITOR'S LOG, DIALOGUE SUMMARY

1082
01:21:08,446 --> 01:21:10,490
I had to write some of them from memory.

1083
01:21:14,327 --> 01:21:17,789
This is all I can do.

1084
01:21:26,172 --> 01:21:28,884
You have until morning call.

1085
01:21:52,240 --> 01:21:53,199
Stop there.

1086
01:21:56,870 --> 01:21:57,746
Me?

1087
01:21:59,080 --> 01:22:01,499
No rest for the weary, right?

1088
01:22:02,375 --> 01:22:04,878
I'm with the Ministry of Justice.

1089
01:22:08,632 --> 01:22:11,217
That's just my magazine.

1090
01:22:11,301 --> 01:22:12,385
You're a prison guard?

1091
01:22:12,886 --> 01:22:15,764
You look more like…

1092
01:22:16,765 --> 01:22:19,267
Like I belong on the
other side of the bars.

1093
01:22:20,226 --> 01:22:25,023
I think the prisoners leave
a stink on me or something.

1094
01:22:25,982 --> 01:22:27,150
What's this?

1095
01:22:27,233 --> 01:22:30,487
I got it to help pass time.

1096
01:22:32,948 --> 01:22:35,533
-Pass.
-Thank you, officers.

1097
01:22:37,911 --> 01:22:41,414
-Nothing like the tabloid to kill time.
-Digest is better.

1098
01:22:42,040 --> 01:22:44,125
<i>The Reader's Digest.</i>

1099
01:22:53,051 --> 01:22:54,594
Bitch Six just left the temple.

1100
01:22:55,261 --> 01:22:57,889
-I thought Kim Jung-nam was Catholic.
-So did I.

1101
01:22:59,265 --> 01:23:00,475
Go check it out.

1102
01:23:04,312 --> 01:23:05,605
You take the back.

1103
01:23:07,107 --> 01:23:09,693
Shouldn't we report it first?
What if we move without--

1104
01:23:09,776 --> 01:23:14,489
Do you want someone else
to get the credit? Just go on.

1105
01:24:00,076 --> 01:24:02,620
<i>Target spotted! Repeat, target spotted!</i>

1106
01:24:32,776 --> 01:24:35,320
Around the back.
He's wearing workman's clothes.

1107
01:24:44,746 --> 01:24:46,331
I swear he was here.

1108
01:24:47,957 --> 01:24:50,001
-Damn it.
-Hey.

1109
01:24:50,585 --> 01:24:51,461
Get up there.

1110
01:25:05,475 --> 01:25:07,352
Where the fuck did he go?

1111
01:25:16,945 --> 01:25:18,780
Confirm position of the target.

1112
01:25:19,572 --> 01:25:21,533
<i>He's not here.</i>

1113
01:25:23,827 --> 01:25:26,746
<i>Checking the area. He's not here.</i>

1114
01:25:30,792 --> 01:25:31,709
Goddammit!

1115
01:25:41,052 --> 01:25:42,178
Damn it.

1116
01:26:03,992 --> 01:26:06,119
<i>Get your asses up here. Now!</i>

1117
01:26:06,202 --> 01:26:07,495
For crying out loud.

1118
01:26:14,085 --> 01:26:16,880
KIM JUNG-NAM

1119
01:26:23,845 --> 01:26:24,762
I'm sorry, sir.

1120
01:26:39,152 --> 01:26:40,028
Director!

1121
01:26:44,324 --> 01:26:46,201
Did Mr. Kim evacuate to safety?

1122
01:26:46,284 --> 01:26:48,745
<i>Yes. He managed to give them a slip.</i>

1123
01:26:49,662 --> 01:26:51,289
Thank goodness for that.

1124
01:26:51,372 --> 01:26:53,124
<i>He's taking refuge in
Hyanglim Church for now.</i>

1125
01:26:53,208 --> 01:26:55,043
I know the place. I'll visit him there…

1126
01:26:55,126 --> 01:26:56,252
<i>No, no…</i>

1127
01:26:56,336 --> 01:26:57,212
I'm home.

1128
01:26:57,295 --> 01:27:00,256
<i>No, it'd be too risky for you
to contact him now.</i>

1129
01:27:00,340 --> 01:27:01,507
Where is Mom?

1130
01:27:01,591 --> 01:27:04,344
<i>Jung-nam's statement
will not have any effect</i>

1131
01:27:04,427 --> 01:27:05,720
<i>without that information.</i>

1132
01:27:07,055 --> 01:27:09,015
<i>-It's really important to have it.</i>
-Wait.

1133
01:27:09,599 --> 01:27:12,310
<i>All our people are
under heavy surveillance.</i>

1134
01:27:13,269 --> 01:27:16,147
I'll find another way
to pass on the message.

1135
01:27:30,328 --> 01:27:31,329
Yeon-hee.

1136
01:27:32,664 --> 01:27:33,581
Yeon-hee!

1137
01:27:35,166 --> 01:27:36,084
You scared me.

1138
01:27:38,378 --> 01:27:39,295
What do you want?

1139
01:27:48,221 --> 01:27:49,138
I'm not doing it.

1140
01:27:49,639 --> 01:27:52,850
I swear this is the last time.

1141
01:27:52,934 --> 01:27:54,727
It's important. He needs to see this.

1142
01:27:54,811 --> 01:27:56,896
What's the point? Only you'll end up hurt.

1143
01:27:56,980 --> 01:27:59,816
How can I do nothing
when there is something I can do?

1144
01:28:05,488 --> 01:28:08,241
I'm not alone in this.
There are people working together.

1145
01:28:09,117 --> 01:28:11,327
Don't you know how my father died?

1146
01:28:12,870 --> 01:28:15,957
All his colleagues ran away
at the first sign of trouble.

1147
01:28:16,040 --> 01:28:19,168
He stood up for what was right.

1148
01:28:19,252 --> 01:28:23,923
The company that didn't pay the wages
should be blamed, not the others.

1149
01:28:24,007 --> 01:28:25,967
He didn't start drinking
because of the company.

1150
01:28:27,635 --> 01:28:31,889
He drank because of the people
that betrayed him.

1151
01:28:32,974 --> 01:28:33,891
Yeon-hee.

1152
01:28:35,935 --> 01:28:37,895
It was an accident.

1153
01:28:37,979 --> 01:28:39,772
It was no one's fault.

1154
01:28:39,856 --> 01:28:41,649
Bullshit!

1155
01:28:43,484 --> 01:28:45,903
If they hadn't abandoned him…

1156
01:28:51,701 --> 01:28:53,703
he wouldn't have died.

1157
01:28:55,621 --> 01:28:57,248
You can take this back.

1158
01:29:14,599 --> 01:29:16,392
It's 250 won. You're 50-won short.

1159
01:29:24,192 --> 01:29:26,069
Go on, have a good life.

1160
01:29:28,321 --> 01:29:29,906
Careful, dears.

1161
01:29:30,573 --> 01:29:33,409
Where is your uncle?

1162
01:29:33,493 --> 01:29:34,535
I don't know.

1163
01:29:35,411 --> 01:29:37,497
Byung-yong!

1164
01:29:38,331 --> 01:29:41,042
Help me move the stalls inside.
It's going to rain tonight.

1165
01:29:44,587 --> 01:29:45,755
Did you two fight?

1166
01:29:45,838 --> 01:29:47,548
Of course not.

1167
01:29:49,842 --> 01:29:54,013
How many times do I have to tell you?

1168
01:29:54,097 --> 01:29:56,849
He's practically a father to you.

1169
01:29:58,226 --> 01:29:59,727
Oh my god!

1170
01:30:00,561 --> 01:30:02,188
-Byung-yong!
-Who are you people?

1171
01:30:02,271 --> 01:30:04,107
You little rat!

1172
01:30:04,690 --> 01:30:05,608
Byung-yong!

1173
01:30:05,691 --> 01:30:07,360
-You fucking bitch!
-No, don't!

1174
01:30:07,902 --> 01:30:11,114
-Get off me.
-Help!

1175
01:30:11,197 --> 01:30:13,866
-Get off of me.
-Please!

1176
01:30:14,450 --> 01:30:15,493
Come here.

1177
01:30:15,576 --> 01:30:17,453
No, please stop. Byung-yong!

1178
01:30:21,541 --> 01:30:23,668
-You fucking son of a bitch.
-Stop!

1179
01:30:24,377 --> 01:30:26,003
What's going on?

1180
01:30:26,087 --> 01:30:27,755
-I didn't do…
-Shut up!

1181
01:30:28,381 --> 01:30:30,550
-Uncle!
-Take him!

1182
01:30:34,345 --> 01:30:35,263
No!

1183
01:30:35,346 --> 01:30:36,973
Search the place.

1184
01:30:38,599 --> 01:30:40,685
Byung-yong!

1185
01:30:40,768 --> 01:30:43,271
I'm okay. Don't worry.

1186
01:30:43,354 --> 01:30:44,480
-Uncle!
-Byung-yong!

1187
01:30:44,564 --> 01:30:46,023
-Yeon-hee!
-Uncle!

1188
01:30:51,112 --> 01:30:52,530
How can they do this?

1189
01:31:00,121 --> 01:31:02,540
Did you see my men at the prison?

1190
01:31:05,126 --> 01:31:06,627
I've seen them a couple of times.

1191
01:31:14,385 --> 01:31:17,138
Do you know Kim Jung-nam?

1192
01:31:19,807 --> 01:31:21,225
I don't know who that is.

1193
01:31:24,604 --> 01:31:28,733
Kim Jung-nam received
money from Kim Il Sung

1194
01:31:29,567 --> 01:31:31,527
and split it with the opposition leaders.

1195
01:31:33,738 --> 01:31:34,697
Is that correct?

1196
01:31:35,573 --> 01:31:37,783
I… don't know that man.

1197
01:31:44,832 --> 01:31:46,334
KIM JUNG-NAM SPY RING

1198
01:31:59,138 --> 01:32:01,182
I thought you didn't know
who I was talking about.

1199
01:32:03,809 --> 01:32:04,852
Get him out of here.

1200
01:32:07,730 --> 01:32:08,731
Two cushions?

1201
01:32:08,814 --> 01:32:11,400
I'll show you how it's done.

1202
01:32:24,872 --> 01:32:25,831
Goal!

1203
01:32:30,920 --> 01:32:33,089
Let me tell you something.

1204
01:32:33,923 --> 01:32:35,925
This room's got a history. A bad history.

1205
01:32:36,008 --> 01:32:38,678
So let's finish quickly
and walk out of here alive, okay?

1206
01:32:47,353 --> 01:32:48,521
Evening papers!

1207
01:32:57,405 --> 01:33:01,534
CONFLICT AGAINST 4.13 STATEMENT
BETWEEN RULING AND OPPOSITION PARTY

1208
01:33:03,077 --> 01:33:04,453
You live high up.

1209
01:33:13,004 --> 01:33:14,297
Why did you come here?

1210
01:33:17,425 --> 01:33:19,135
I came to recruit you, of course.

1211
01:33:20,678 --> 01:33:22,054
Join our cartoon club.

1212
01:33:23,264 --> 01:33:24,849
Jung-mi just joined too.

1213
01:33:29,562 --> 01:33:31,314
We made this at the club.

1214
01:33:32,898 --> 01:33:34,483
APPEAL AGAINST DICTATORSHIP AND TORTURE

1215
01:33:42,325 --> 01:33:43,743
Are you going to protest?

1216
01:33:48,998 --> 01:33:51,083
You think you can change the world?

1217
01:33:52,001 --> 01:33:55,671
Your ideal and dreams…
Don't you think about your family?

1218
01:34:03,679 --> 01:34:05,348
"WHEN THE DAY COMES"

1219
01:34:06,265 --> 01:34:08,059
No such day will come.

1220
01:34:10,603 --> 01:34:12,438
Stop dreaming and wake up.

1221
01:34:16,942 --> 01:34:18,527
I wish I could,

1222
01:34:21,781 --> 01:34:23,240
but I can't.

1223
01:34:29,330 --> 01:34:31,040
Because it hurts too much.

1224
01:34:36,629 --> 01:34:37,546
You should go.

1225
01:34:48,349 --> 01:34:49,266
See you.

1226
01:34:55,481 --> 01:34:56,524
Yeon-hee!

1227
01:34:58,275 --> 01:35:00,069
Call me if you change your mind.

1228
01:35:35,104 --> 01:35:38,482
CALL ME
THIS IS MY NUMBER!

1229
01:36:02,590 --> 01:36:04,508
THIS IS THE LAST TIME.
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT.

1230
01:36:04,592 --> 01:36:06,343
FIND KIM JUNG-NAM AT HYANGLIM CHURCH

1231
01:36:18,939 --> 01:36:19,982
Hello?

1232
01:36:20,065 --> 01:36:21,025
<i>Yeon-hee.</i>

1233
01:36:23,027 --> 01:36:25,905
What's wrong, Mom? What happened?

1234
01:36:25,988 --> 01:36:29,992
<i>Your uncle's been taken to Namyeong-dong
by the same people</i>

1235
01:36:30,784 --> 01:36:32,786
<i>that killed that student.</i>

1236
01:36:34,997 --> 01:36:36,957
That bastard won't give in.

1237
01:36:37,750 --> 01:36:39,126
Can you do another round?

1238
01:36:43,547 --> 01:36:46,300
We worked him over seven times,
and he still gave us nothing.

1239
01:36:46,383 --> 01:36:48,552
He's a tenacious bastard, huh?

1240
01:36:48,636 --> 01:36:49,887
Bring me his file.

1241
01:36:59,730 --> 01:37:00,940
What's going on?

1242
01:37:05,027 --> 01:37:06,987
Get out of my way!

1243
01:37:07,071 --> 01:37:09,281
I know he's here.

1244
01:37:09,365 --> 01:37:12,576
I'm here, Byung-yong!

1245
01:37:12,660 --> 01:37:16,121
-Free them all!
-Your sister's here!

1246
01:37:16,205 --> 01:37:18,958
-Free them all!
-Why do you hold them up there?

1247
01:37:19,041 --> 01:37:20,251
Stop them.

1248
01:37:20,334 --> 01:37:22,044
Give my brother back!

1249
01:37:22,127 --> 01:37:23,963
Keep these people out.

1250
01:37:25,839 --> 01:37:28,050
Are you all right?

1251
01:37:28,133 --> 01:37:29,176
My brother…

1252
01:37:29,260 --> 01:37:30,886
Mom! You all right?

1253
01:37:30,970 --> 01:37:34,557
How dare you hit her?

1254
01:37:34,640 --> 01:37:39,103
What are you, some kind of thug?

1255
01:37:40,312 --> 01:37:41,814
Mom, no!

1256
01:37:43,482 --> 01:37:46,402
How dare you hit her?

1257
01:37:51,156 --> 01:37:52,157
Mom!

1258
01:37:55,703 --> 01:37:56,579
Yeon-hee!

1259
01:37:57,746 --> 01:37:59,081
Get inside!

1260
01:37:59,164 --> 01:38:01,125
-You can't do this!
-Yeon-hee!

1261
01:38:02,835 --> 01:38:04,378
Mom!

1262
01:38:05,004 --> 01:38:09,008
Shut up, you bitches!

1263
01:38:10,676 --> 01:38:12,303
To positions!

1264
01:39:33,258 --> 01:39:34,718
HWAJEONG BARBERSHOP

1265
01:40:36,029 --> 01:40:37,322
Stop!

1266
01:40:38,115 --> 01:40:38,949
Sir!

1267
01:40:43,328 --> 01:40:50,169
Two, three, four, five, six, seven.

1268
01:41:01,638 --> 01:41:05,434
One, two, three,

1269
01:41:05,517 --> 01:41:08,854
four, five, six.

1270
01:41:25,871 --> 01:41:27,956
See this kid standing next to my mother?

1271
01:41:32,920 --> 01:41:34,630
His name is Dong.

1272
01:41:36,131 --> 01:41:40,636
We found him starving to death,
